<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1142">
A fence consists of $n$ vertical boards. The width of each board is 1 and their heights may vary.<br />
<br />
You want to attach a rectangular advertisement to the fence. What is the maximum area of such an advertisement?<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line contains an integer $n$: the width of the fence.<br />
<br />
After this, there are $n$ integers $k_1,k_2,\ldots,k_n$: the height of each board.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print one integer: the maximum area of an advertisement.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 2 \cdot 10^5$<br />
<li>$1 \le k_i \le 10^9$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>8<br />
4 1 5 3 3 2 4 1</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>10</code>    </div>
